title: Lena Dunham joins California Democrats and Planned Parenthood for Pink Out Day
text:
Lena Dunham joins California Democrats and Planned Parenthood for Pink Out Day Posted at 7:53 pm on January 17, 2017 by William A. Share on Facebook Share on Twitter 
The Legislative Women’s Caucus of the California Legislative Assembly led a rally in support of Planned Parenthood in Sacramento, Calif., Tuesday. Guests included actress Lena Dunham and activists representing Planned Parenthood. 
Organizers said the purpose of the rally was “to show solidarity to protect health care access for nearly 1 million Californians” and to demonstrate support for Planned Parenthood “and the lifesaving care it provides to millions of men and women.” We'll be LIVE on Facebook at 11:30 with @PPActionCA : https://t.co/74SqlJDSUc pic.twitter.com/uXBCuDVwjJ 
— Assembly Democrats (@AssemblyDems) January 17, 2017 Thinking about bringing @lenadunham on as chief selfie-taker. #StandWithPP pic.twitter.com/kbNlUK4qjv 
— Anthony Rendon (@Rendon63rd) January 17, 2017 CA Senate now discussing, as did Assembly earlier today, resolution supporting Planned Parenthood.. part of big day of Sac support. 
— John Myers (@johnmyers) January 17, 2017 Girls actress @lenadunham on the assembly floor w/ women's caucus chair @AsmGarcia pic.twitter.com/ICtmhTSwuC 
— Laurel Rosenhall (@LaurelRosenhall) January 17, 2017 Lena Dunham speaking in support of Planned Parenthood at Pink Out Day at the California State Capitol #IStandWithPP pic.twitter.com/EjNFEGSnOI
